The abducted director of the Lagos State Fire Service,  Mr Musbau Rasak has been freed. New Telegraph gathered that kidnapped the fire boss was dumped on Itokin-Epe Road around 12 am. The fire boss was reportedly kidnapped on Saturday on his way to Epe by the gunmen who later disappeared through the waterways near the cenotaph erected in honour of the victims of the ill-fated ADC crash on November 7, 1996 around 8 pm. Following Musibau’s abduction, New Telegraph gathered that residents and motorists travelling to the remote areas in the state, especially Epe and other suburbs close to the creeks had expressed concerns on the possibility of kidnappers to operate freely in the state specifically during the transition period. The State’s Commissioner of Police,  Zubairu Muazu, denied resurgence of kidnappers in the state.
